**Code Explanation:**

The code implements a GPU-accelerated 2D pseudo-spectral Navier-Stokes solver using PyTorch. It solves the vorticity-streamfunction equation with hyperviscosity and Ekman drag. The DNS_Solver class handles the vorticity-streamfunction equation, velocity computation, and RK4 time integration. The get_k_grid function generates the wavenumber grid. The code implements the full production run, including tracer seeding and advection. Tracers are initialized uniformly at the end of the spinup phase. The production loop runs for T_prod = 50 * T_L, saving tracer positions to disk using np.memmap. The velocity field is used to advect tracers via bilinear interpolation.

